snippet: The United States Justice Department said on Tuesday that it was investigating the death of Victor White III, 23, who died while in custody of Iberia Parish sheriff’s deputies in March.
abstract: Justice Department is investigating the death of Victor White III, young Louisiana man who died while in the custody of Iberia Parish sheriff’s deputies; local coroner in Louisiana determined that White's shooting death in the back of a police cruiser while his hands were cuffed was suicide.
lead_paragraph: The United States Justice Department said on Tuesday that it was investigating the death of Victor White III, 23, who died while in custody of Iberia Parish sheriff’s deputies in March.

headline.main: Louisiana: U.S. Joins Inquiry Into Death in Police Car
headline.print_headline: Louisiana: U.S. Joins Inquiry Into Death in Police Car
